MODULE 1: Introduction to Data Analytics

This module helps beginners understand what Data Analytics is, why it is important, and how companies use data to make business decisions.

1. What is Data Analytics?
Definition

Data Analytics is the process of collecting, cleaning, organizing, analyzing, and interpreting data to discover useful information and support decision-making.

Simple Definition

Data Analytics means converting raw data into meaningful insights.

Real-Life Example

Suppose you own a supermarket.

Every day customers buy products like:

Milk
Bread
Rice
Biscuits
Soft Drinks

After one month, you analyze the sales.

You discover:

Milk sells most in the morning.
Soft drinks sell more during summer.
Biscuits sell more on weekends.

Now you can:

Stock more milk every morning.
Increase soft drink inventory in summer.
Offer weekend biscuit discounts.

This is Data Analytics.

